column4: I'm installing kate on (gnome)ubuntu 10.04, and it seems to be stuck at: kbuildsycoca4(4788) kdemain: Emitting notifyDatabaseChanged ("servicetypes", "xdgdata-mime", "services", "apps")
it's just updating the settings cache
can I just ^C out of it?
I doubt that'll do anything, kate runs in the background usually
I thought this was in the apt-get
I can't check though, because it's filled the terminal's buffer
if you just press return do you get your prompt?
apt-get installed some files which caused kbuildsyscoca to go "ooh new files, best update myself" and it printed some debugging stuff while doing the update
you probably started a KDE app on the same terminal earlier so kbuildsycoca outputs to that terminal
I should fix it so it doesn't output needless debugging by default
